'''理想國演藝股份有限公司'''（{{lang-en|Live Nation Entertainment, Inc}}）簡稱'''理想國演藝'''或'''理想國'''（Live Nation）是一家全球性的[[娛樂|娛樂]]公司，由音樂展演公司{{tsl|en|Live Nation (events promoter)|理想國 (音樂展演)|理想國}}和票務發售公司{{tsl|en|Ticketmaster|票務大師}}於2010年合併成立，總部位於[[美國|美國]][[比佛利山|比佛利山]]。該公司擁有、租賃、營運大量的美國娛樂場館。領導層包括董事長{{tsl|en|Greg Maffei|格雷格·馬菲}}（兼任{{tsl|en|Liberty Media|自由傳媒}}執行長）和加拿大籍總裁、執行長{{tsl|en|Michael Rapino|邁克爾·拉皮諾}}。

== 歷史 ==
2009年，音樂展演公司{{tsl|en|Live Nation (events promoter)|理想國 (音樂展演)|理想國}}和票務發售公司{{tsl|en|Ticketmaster|票務大師}}達成合併協議並得到監管部門同意，新成立的公司被命名為理想國演藝（Live Nation Entertainment）。<ref>{{Cite web |title=British Regulator Supports Live Nation-Ticketmaster Merger |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/23/business/global/23ticketmaster.html |accessdate=2021-04-25 |date=2009-12-22 |last=Nicholson |first=Chris V. |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |archive-date=2021-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309014714/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/23/business/global/23ticketmaster.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Nation, Ticketmaster merger official |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/live-nation-ticketmaster-merger-official-79083 |accessdate=2021-04-25 |date=2009-02-10 |language=en |website=The Hollywood Reporter |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308080228/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/live-nation-ticketmaster-merger-official-79083 |dead-url=no }}</ref>理想國公司原執行長{{tsl|en|Michael Rapino|邁克爾·拉皮諾}}被任命為理想國演藝首任執行長，Ticketmaster原執行長{{tsl|en|Irving Azoff|伊夫琳·阿佐夫}}則成為董事會[[董事長#其他職權|執行主席]]。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ticketmaster-livenation-idUSTRE5194DL20090210 |title=Live Nation to buy Ticketmaster |author=Yinka Adegoke |publisher=Reuters |date=2009-02-10 |language=en |editor1=Derek Caney |editor2=Tiffany Wu |editor3=Richard Chang |access-date=2019-07-16 |location=紐約 |archive-date=2020-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803151716/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ticketmaster-livenation-idUSTRE5194DL20090210 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

合併案首先於2009年獲得[[挪威|挪威]]和[[土耳其|土耳其]]監管部門的批准<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/live-nation-ticketmaster-merger-approved-in-u-k-182586/|title=Live Nation-Ticketmaster Merger Approved in U.K.|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=2009-12-22|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-16|archive-date=2021-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309062944/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/live-nation-ticketmaster-merger-approved-in-u-k-182586/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；[[英國|英國]]{{tsl|en|Competition Commission|競爭委員會 (英國)|競爭委員會}}於2009年10月臨時否決兩公司的合併案<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wired.com/epicenter/2009/10/live-nationticketmaster-merger-faces-obstacles-here-and-abroad/|title=Live Nation/Ticketmaster Merger Faces Obstacles Here and Abroad|date=2009-10-12|work=Wired|accessdate=2009-10-19|author=Van Buskirk, Eliot|language=en|archive-date=2012-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114064904/http://www.wired.com/epicenter/2009/10/live-nationticketmaster-merger-faces-obstacles-here-and-abroad/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但於同年12月22日撤回該決議允許雙方合併。<ref name=":0" />

合併案在美國則受到部分監管部門、[[藝人|藝人]]、歌迷和競爭公司的反對，其認為此舉會降低同業間的競爭及增加票務成本。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bruce-springsteen-furious-at-ticketmaster-rails-against-live-nation-merger-97368/|title=Bruce Springsteen "Furious" At Ticketmaster, Rails Against Live Nation Merger|last=Kreps|first=Daniel|date=2009-02-04|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-16|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128053424/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bruce-springsteen-furious-at-ticketmaster-rails-against-live-nation-merger-97368/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ticketnews.com/Ticketmaster-Live-Nation-merger-twenty-five-thousand-contact-DOJ-to-oppose-the-deal11019818|title=Ticketmaster / Live Nation merger: 25,000 contact DOJ to oppose the deal|author=Branch, Alfred Jr.|date=2010-01-19|access-date=2010-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100122153341/http://www.ticketnews.com/Ticketmaster-Live-Nation-merger-twenty-five-thousand-contact-DOJ-to-oppose-the-deal11019818|archive-date=2010-01-22|dead-url=yes|publisher=TicketNews|language=en}}</ref>[[搖滾|搖滾]]歌手[[布魯斯·史普林斯汀|布魯斯·史普林斯汀]]是當時合併案的主要反對者。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2009/02/04/bruce-springsteen-furious-at-ticketmaster-rails-against-live-nation-merger/|title=Bruce Springsteen "Furious" At Ticketmaster, Rails Against Live Nation Merger|date=2009-02-04|access-date=2009-10-19|publisher=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|archive-date=2009-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091012054546/http://www.rollingstone.com/rockdaily/index.php/2009/02/04/bruce-springsteen-furious-at-ticketmaster-rails-against-live-nation-merger/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年1月25日，[[美國司法部|美國司法部]]批准兩公司的合併案，但必須滿足部份條件。<ref name="Chmielewski">{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-ct-ticketmaster26-2010jan26,0,5237319,full.story|title=Ticketmaster-Live Nation merger gets Justice Department's approval|author=Chmielewski, Dawn C. and Fritz, Ben and Lewis, Randy|date=2010-01-26|access-date=2010-01-26|publisher=The Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|archive-date=2010-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100129062607/http://www.latimes.com/business/la-fi-ct-ticketmaster26-2010jan26,0,5237319,full.story|dead-url=yes}}</ref>包括票務大師需出售旗下的自助售票公司{{tsl|en|Comcast Spectacor|Comcast Spectacor|Paciolan}}的所有權<ref name="Chmielewski" />，並將其軟體專利授權予[[安舒茨娛樂集團|安舒茨娛樂集團]]，這將使該公司在業務上具有與票務大師「正面競爭」的能力<ref name=":1">{{cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/epicenter/2010/01/doj-approves-modified-ticketmaster-live-nation-merger/|title=DOJ Approves Modified Ticketmaster, Live Nation Merger|author=Van Buskirk, Eliot|date=2010-01-25|work=Wired News|access-date=2010-01-26|language=en|archive-date=2012-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120602213713/http://www.wired.com/epicenter/2010/01/doj-approves-modified-ticketmaster-live-nation-merger|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/26/business/26ticket.html|title=Justice Dept. Clears Ticketmaster-Live Nation Merger|last=Sisario|first=Ben|date=2010-01-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-07-16|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308141849/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/26/business/26ticket.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而安舒茨娛樂則可在5年後選擇收購該軟體或以其它物件取代，抑或是尋求其它票務公司的合作。<ref name=":1" />此外，理想國演藝受一部為期10年的法院命令規範，禁止該公司對選擇接受其競爭公司票務合約的場所進行商業報復。<ref name=":3" />

=== 投資與擴大 ===
2013年，理想國演藝收購{{tsl|en|Voodoo Music + Arts Experience|巫毒音樂和藝術體驗}}音樂節，並宣布與[[電子舞曲|電子舞曲]]籌辦公司{{tsl|en|Insomniac (promoter)|Insomniac (音樂展演)|Insomniac}}成立[[合資公司|合資公司]]。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spin.com/2013/06/electric-daisy-carnival-insomniac-dick-clark-productions-edm-awards-2014/ |title=Electric Daisy Chain: Insomniac and Dick Clark Prod. Plan 2014 EDM Awards |author=Philip Sherburne |publisher=Spin |date=2013-06-21 |language=en |access-date=2018-08-11 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155352/https://www.spin.com/2013/06/electric-daisy-carnival-insomniac-dick-clark-productions-edm-awards-2014/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/branding/1567396/live-nation-teams-with-insomniac-events-in-creative-partnership |title=Live Nation Teams With Insomniac Events in 'Creative Partnership' |author=Zel McCarthy |work=Billboard |date=2013-06-20 |location=洛杉磯 |language=en |access-date=2018-08-11 |archive-date=2019-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404230920/https://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/branding/1567396/live-nation-teams-with-insomniac-events-in-creative-partnership |dead-url=yes }}</ref>此外又先後於2014年收購{{tsl|en|C3 Presents|C3 Presents}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6414053/live-nation-completes-deal-for-c3-presents |title=Live Nation Completes Deal for C3 Presents |author=Lars Brandle |work=Billboard |date=2014-12-22 |language=en |access-date=2017-10-28 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155354/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/6414053/live-nation-completes-deal-for-c3-presents |dead-url=no }}</ref>、2015年買下[[波納羅音樂節|波納羅音樂節]]的控股權<ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Nation Entertainment buys controlling stake in Bonnaroo festival |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-live-nation-buys-controlling-stake-in-bonnaroo-20150428-story.html |date=2015-04-28 |last=Faughnder |first=Ryan |publisher=The  Los Angeles Times |language=en-US |access-date=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155352/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-live-nation-buys-controlling-stake-in-bonnaroo-20150428-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、2016年收購州長舞會音樂節（Governors Ball Music Festival）母公司Founders Entertainment的多數股份<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/11/business/media/live-nation-adds-governors-ball-to-its-music-festival-lineup.html/ |title=Live Nation Adds Governors Ball to Its Music Festival Lineup |last=Sisario |first=Ben |publisher=The New York Time |date=2016-04-11 |language=en-US |access-date=2018-10-15 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155352/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/11/business/media/live-nation-adds-governors-ball-to-its-music-festival-lineup.html/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，以及於2016年10月收購位於[[田納西州|田納西州]][[諾克斯維爾|諾克斯維爾]]的及時娛樂（AC Entertainment）及若干跨國公司。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/money/2016/10/31/live-nation-buys-ac-entertainment/93074100/ |title=Live Nation buys AC Entertainment |author=Nate Rau |date=2016-10-31 |newspaper=The Tennessean |language=en |access-date=2016-11-16 |archive-date=2021-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501143429/https://www.tennessean.com/story/money/2016/10/31/live-nation-buys-ac-entertainment/93074100/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=":5" />理想國演藝於2017年持續投資[[音樂節|音樂節]]及籌辦公司，並購入BottleRock Napa Valley音樂節<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/Live-Nation-acquires-major-stake-in-BottleRock-10853961.php |title=Live Nation acquires major stake in BottleRock festival |author=Aidin Vaziri |publisher=SF Chronicle |date=2017-06-13 |language=en |access-date=2018-08-11 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155353/https://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/Live-Nation-acquires-major-stake-in-BottleRock-10853961.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[鹽湖城|鹽湖城]]音樂籌辦及巡演公司United Concerts和CT Touring的多數股份。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Nation acquires Salt Lake's United Concerts |url=https://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/music/live-nation-acquires-salt-lake-s-united-concerts/article_aeba440c-9fe6-55b9-921a-8e3f21ddb343.html |date=2017-10-04 |last=Fox |first=Doug |language=en |website=Daily Herald |access-date=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155353/https://www.heraldextra.com/entertainment/music/live-nation-acquires-salt-lake-s-united-concerts/article_aeba440c-9fe6-55b9-921a-8e3f21ddb343.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/01/live-nation-acquires-ct-touring/|title=Live Nation acquires CT Touring|date=2017-01-20|website=IQ Magazine|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-17|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427155354/https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/01/live-nation-acquires-ct-touring/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年，理想國演藝報告的營收為103億[[美元|美元]]。<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Nation Reports Over $10 Billion in Revenue in 2017 Financial Earnings |url=http://www.ampthemag.com/the-real/live-nation-reports-10-billion-revenue-2017-financial-earnings/ |author=Taylor Mims |date=2018-02-27 |language=en-US |website=Amplify |access-date=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2020-02-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217195245/http://www.ampthemag.com/the-real/live-nation-reports-10-billion-revenue-2017-financial-earnings/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>2018年，該公司透過併購其它娛樂公司的方式擴大其音樂籌辦部門，其中包括Frank Productions<ref>{{Cite web |title=Madison-based concert promoter Frank Productions selling majority interest to Live Nation |url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/entertainment/music/2018/01/11/madison-based-concert-promoter-frank-productions-selling-majority-interest-live-nation/1025688001/ |accessdate=2021-04-27 |date=2018-01-11 |last=Levy |first=Piet |publisher=Milwaukee Journal Sentinel |language=en-US |archive-date=2020-09-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918090033/https://www.jsonline.com/story/entertainment/music/2018/01/11/madison-based-concert-promoter-frank-productions-selling-majority-interest-live-nation/1025688001/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>、Emporium Presents和Red Mountain Entertainment等公司。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8477654/live-nation-acquires-emporium-presents |title=Live Nation Acquires Emporium Presents |author=Starr Bowenbank |work=Billboard |date=2018-10-01 |language=en |access-date=2018-12-12 |archive-date=2021-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427170846/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8477654/live-nation-acquires-emporium-presents |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Live Nation buys Red Mountain Entertainment, Birmingham's largest concert promoter |url=https://www.al.com/entertainment/2018/06/live_nation_buys_birminghams_l.html |date=2018-06-27 |last=Colurso |first=Mary |language=en-US |website=AL.com |access-date=2019-07-17 |archive-date=2021-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316191913/https://www.al.com/entertainment/2018/06/live_nation_buys_birminghams_l.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

